<item>
            <title>[LU-10314] implement ladvise dontneed for ZFS</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10314</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;lfs ladvise&lt;/tt&gt; functionality was added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-4931&quot; title=&quot;New feature of giving server/storage side advice of accessing file&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-4931&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-4931&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; to allow the client to prefetch data into OSS cache via &lt;tt&gt;willread&lt;/tt&gt; and to drop it from cache via &lt;tt&gt;dontneed&lt;/tt&gt;.  ZFS has functionality to implement &lt;tt&gt;willread&lt;/tt&gt;, but is missing the &lt;tt&gt;dontneed&lt;/tt&gt; functionality to drop pages from the OSS cache.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
